  <p class="content"><p>"onboard terminal encourages the driver to correct his or her behaviors"</p>
<p>The key word here is encourages.  The kind of drivers that are causing the problem are the kind of drivers that will ignore the onboard terminal.</p>
<p>In cities where traffic congestion is a problem, drivers are more aggressive.  Aggressive drivers don't like other cars getting in front of them, so they tailgate.  They also believe the car in front of them will go faster if they tailgate (I like to troll tailgaters by slowing down).</p>
<p>Sorry, I think aggressive drivers are going to drive aggressively regardless of the onboard terminal's encouragement.</p>
