<p>So what happens typically now? A contest begins, the aggressive driver behind them rides high on their tale, extremely close. But, it just not one car making the contest, it is a line of cars really close to each other, all in the left lane. Then the unpredictable happens and an accident occurs that involves a pile up of cars. These accidents many times are so bad, they make national news.</p>
<p>I often see this type of driving and trains of close cars on the highway often.</p>
